T1  - The Multinomial Option Pricing Model and Its Brownian and Poisson Limits
PY  - 1989
Y1  - 1989/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/2.2.251
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 2
IS  - 2
SP  - 251
EP  - 265
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - The Cox, Ross, and Rubinstein binomial model is generalized to the multinomial case. Limits are investigated and shown to yield the Black-Scholes formula in the case of continuous sample paths for a wide variety of complete market structures. In the discontinuous case of Merton-type formula is shown to result, provided jump probabilities are replaced by their corresponding Arrow-Debreu prices.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/2.2.251
ER  - 



