T1  - Mean Reversion in Short-Horizon Expected Returns
PY  - 1989
Y1  - 1989/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/2.2.225
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 2
IS  - 2
SP  - 225
EP  - 240
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article develops and estimates a simple model for monthly expected stock returns that relies on the rapidly decaying structure of shorter-horizon (weekly) expected returns. The most striking aspect of our finds is that the rapid mean reversion in short-horizon expected returns implies much greater variation through time in monthly expected returns than has been documented in earlier studies. For instance, during the 1962 to 1985 period, over 25 percent of the return variance of small firms can be explained by time variation in expected returns.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/2.2.225
ER  - 



